-- Lula Says Brazil Bank Interest Rates Need to Fall to International Levels
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-11-02T11:37:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/lula-says-brazil-bank-interest-rates-need-to-fall-to-international-levels.html
Brazilian President Luiz Inacio Lula
da Silva said interest rates charged by the country’s banks need
to fall further to approach international levels.  The next government must continue Lula’s work to cut
interest rates without “losing sight of the battle against
inflation,” the president said in his weekly column on the
presidency’s website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price in London at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
